# Test Analysis: region_manager

## Spec
docs/specs/core/world/region_manager.h.spec.md

## Test Report
scripts/test_report_digest/test_suite_world_region_manager.c.report

## Source
core/source/world/region_manager.c

## Failures

### 1. `initialize_region_manager` does not initialize `center_of__region_manager`

**Assertion failed:**
  manager.center_of__region_manager.x__i32 == 0 (-1029559887 == 0)

**Root Cause:**
  `initialize_region_manager` only calls
  `initialize_serialization_header__contiguous_array` on the `regions`
  array. The `center_of__region_manager` field (of type
  `Region_Vector__3i32`) is never initialized, leaving it with
  indeterminate (garbage) memory values.

**Expected Behavior (per spec):**
  `initialize_region_manager` should initialize all regions as
  deallocated AND zero-initialize `center_of__region_manager` so that
  all its components (x, y, z) are 0.

**Fix Required in:**
  `core/source/world/region_manager.c` — `initialize_region_manager`
  must zero-initialize `p_region_manager->center_of__region_manager`
  after initializing the regions array.

## Summary

| # | Function                    | Issue                                      | Severity |
|---|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------|----------|
| 1 | `initialize_region_manager` | `center_of__region_manager` not initialized | High     |
